data.description: Price dropped significantly below value for a quick sale****Back on the market*****HOA is only two payments of $229.50 which equals to $38.25 per month…Home Sweet Home! This is what you will say when you drive into the culdesac, see your 2023 new roof, and park your car in the two-car garage of this beautiful house. 12402 Nathan Ct has been decorated by a professional interior designer, and you'll be very impressed.   As you walk into your home, you can’t help but enjoy the gleaming hardwood floors throughout the first level, stairs, and upstairs hallway. The kitchen with stainless steel appliances, a refrigerator with two built-in icemakers, granite countertops, and beautiful backsplash throughout will make you smile. Walk, don’t run to your owner suite as you make your way upstairs to your getaway, but make sure you say hello to anyone in the three other bedrooms upstairs. The standalone bathtub in the owner’s suite will relax you as you listen to music using the Bluetooth ceiling speaker. Don’t feel like taking a bath; you have a shower that holds two people. The owner suite will amaze you at how well it was renovated in 2021. Complete your me time in the owner suite by relaxing in the basement (with ceiling speakers), enclosed porch (with ceiling speakers), or deck...just pick one. Don’t think about what you must do when you work from home or entertain your visiting guest in the first-floor office/bedroom. Your home is waiting for you to visit and purchase!  ****************************************This house has a new roof (2023), the upper furnace and outside unit were replaced in 2022, the lower furnace outside unit was replaced in 2020, and the hot water heater was replaced in 2017. The home also has custom wood closet organizers in both owner bedroom closets, professionally installed custom wood blinds in every room in the house, the entire deck is made of composite material, and the shed that conveys was purchased and installed in 2020. The seller has leftover paint from when the entire house was painted to help with touchup.******************************************************
